external_knowledge:
- "fresh sprouts" refers to new students who have just started a course;
- "planted their roots" is a metaphorical way of saying that students have enrolled;
- "garden of knowledge" is a metaphor for the educational environment or institution;
- "first course" corresponds to `course_id = 1`.

sql:
SELECT students.student_name, courses.course_name 
FROM students 
INNER JOIN courses ON students.course_id = courses.course_id;

SELECT curriculum_name
FROM curriculum
WHERE week = 1;

SELECT assessment_name 
FROM assessments 
WHERE assessment_id = 123;

external_knowledge:
- "faculty members" refers to the instructors teaching courses;
- "learners" refers to the students enrolled in the courses;
- "enrolled in their classes" implies that the students are associated with the courses taught by each instructor.

sql:
SELECT instructor_name, instructor_id 
FROM instructors 
WHERE instructor_id NOT IN (
  SELECT DISTINCT instructor_id 
  FROM courses
);

SELECT created_by, COUNT(curriculum_id) as NumCurriculumComponents
FROM curriculum
GROUP BY created_by;
